<item>
            <title>[LU-483] Lustre quota not usabe</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-483</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>
&lt;p&gt;The CEA Bull customer is complaining about quota that are not working properly with Luster 2.0 Bull.&lt;br/&gt;
Until last week, quota were disabled because they were experiencing frequent system crashes on some IO servers.&lt;br/&gt;
We delivered an Efix containing the patch proposed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-369&quot; title=&quot;ASSERTION(oti &amp;amp;&amp;amp; oti-&amp;gt;oti_thread &amp;amp;&amp;amp; oti-&amp;gt;oti_thread-&amp;gt;t_watchdog) failed in quota_chk_acq_common()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-369&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-369&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and they re-enabled quota and made some tests.&lt;br/&gt;
There is no longer system crashes, but a user is able to write more than allowed by quotas.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is the description of there tests:&lt;br/&gt;
 1. starting of the fs&lt;br/&gt;
 2. quotaoff/quotacheck/quotaon/quotacheck&lt;br/&gt;
 3. set the quota to a user who has already exceeded it&apos;s quota&lt;br/&gt;
 4. this user is able to continue to write&lt;br/&gt;
 5. set the user quota to a value higher than the actual used capacity&lt;br/&gt;
 6. this user is able to write and to exceed is quota&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I attached the syslog of the IO servers they provided (MDS:curie113, OSS:curie200-207).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
